{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"506ffa5d-52bb-4cac-b178-4a72f09e674f","content":"The standard approach is to **wrap file I/O behind an interface** and inject it:\n\n```csharp\npublic interface IFileSystem\n{\n    string ReadAllText(string path);\n    void WriteAllText(string path, string contents);\n    bool DirectoryExists(string path);\n}\n```\n\nThen create a real implementation that delegates to `System.IO`, and inject `IFileSystem` into your classes. In tests, you mock/fake it.\n\n**Even easier:** use the [`System.IO.Abstractions`](https://www.nuget.org/packages/System.IO.Abstractions) NuGet package — it provides `IFileSystem` and a `MockFileSystem` out of the box, so you don't have to maintain your own wrapper.\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions\ndotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers  # for tests\n```\n\nThen replace `File.ReadAllText(path)` with `_fileSystem.File.ReadAllText(path)`, etc.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"99d792a6-4c07-4984-8aa7-af7474ee1d8f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to make file system operations (`File.WriteAllText`, `File.ReadAllText`, `Directory.Exists`) testable in their .NET project. This is a common software engineering question about testability and dependency injection.\n\nThis is a general advice question - they're not asking me to modify any specific code. I should give them a concise answer about the standard approach.\n\nThe standard approach is to:\n1. Create an interface (e.g., `IFileSystem`) that abstracts file system operations\n2. Implement it with a real implementation that delegates to `System.IO`\n3. Inject the interface where needed\n\n\n4. In tests, provide a mock or fake implementation\n\nThere's also a popular NuGet package called `System.IO.Abstractions` that already provides this abstraction layer, which could save some work if they don't want to build it themselves.","outputTokens":464,"requestId":"8438:1CBFF8:20F8435:24777FE:6A0AD1D4"},"id":"1c5c3493-cdbf-4bbf-a13b-fb4a36d48c45","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:46:22.254Z","parentId":"7697f9ad-5a00-4c83-8060-f19a3df05868"}
